<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Hamilton Lane recently published a strategic plan update for their client, Teachers’ Retirement System of Louisiana, which includes private markets commitment pacing recommendations. The screenshot below shows a “potential” mandate sourced from Nasdaq eVestment’s fundraising solution for asset managers with details on Louisiana Teachers’s private debt investment plan for 2024 and the years to come.</span></span></p>

<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The potential mandate’s source document include additional insights:</span></span></p>

<ul>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><b>Louisiana Teachers is currently under-allocated to direct lending (0.2% vs. 3% target) and distressed debt/mezzanine (7.9% vs. 9% target)</b></span></span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><b>The plan is expected to commit $900 – $1,200 million across 6 – 10 private debt partnerships in FY 2024</b></span></span></li>
</ul>
